    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`Math.random` isn't meant to be cryptographically secure. Trusting on it for any crypto/security related operations isn't a good idea. Geth uses the otto vm which comes with a `Math.random` implementation that uses the `math/rand` package to generate pseudo random floats. There is actually a [PR](https://github.com/robertkrimen/otto/pull/95) in the otto vm repo to use a somewhat better seed.\n",
